aul Biedermann in 2009.\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4738, \"end\": 4753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Biedermann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Biedermann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Biedermann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Biedermann\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4665}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(That was the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csuper-suit\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d era, when now-prohibited buoyant suit material helped rewrite the record book.)\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4873, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csuper-suit\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d era\", \"from\": 4773, \"to\": 4797}, {\"ngram\": \"now-prohibited buoyant suit material\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4840}, {\"ngram\": \"the record book\", \"from\": 4856, \"to\": 4871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The much-hyped showdown in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400 freestyle between Ariarne Titmus of Australia, Summer McIntosh of Canada and Katie Ledecky of the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the three most recent world-record holders\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094was a bit of a dud.\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 5089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4938, \"end\": 4952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 4956, \"end\": 4965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.8435006153528183, \"rank\": 0.18553558273532217, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4967, \"end\": 4982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}, {\"begin\": 4986, \"end\": 4992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9973563972169095, \"rank\": 0.0026393123628961593, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4997, \"end\": 5010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The much-hyped showdown\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4898}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400 freestyle\", \"from\": 4902, \"to\": 4929}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the three most recent world-record\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5059}, {\"ngram\": \"a dud\", \"from\": 5083, \"to\": 5088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None of the three came close to their best times.\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"None\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5094}, {\"ngram\": \"their best times\", \"from\": 5122, \"to\": 5138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bronze medalist Ledecky did not break four minutes for the first time in her career in a major international meet.\", \"from\": 5140, \"to\": 5254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bronze medalist Ledecky\", \"from\": 5140, \"to\": 5163}, {\"ngram\": \"four minutes\", \"from\": 5178, \"to\": 5190}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 5195, \"to\": 5209}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 5213, \"to\": 5223}, {\"ngram\": \"a major international meet\", \"from\": 5227, \"to\": 5253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But digging further into the numbers reveals some inconclusive data.\", \"from\": 5256, \"to\": 5324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the numbers\", \"from\": 5281, \"to\": 5292}, {\"ngram\": \"some inconclusive data\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of the 15 finalized events, seven have been won in faster times than in 2021 and seven in slower times, with one identical winning time.\", \"from\": 5325, \"to\": 5461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 15 finalized events\", \"from\": 5328, \"to\": 5351}, {\"ngram\": \"faster times\", \"from\": 5376, \"to\": 5388}, {\"ngram\": \"slower times\", \"from\": 5415, \"to\": 5427}, {\"ngram\": \"one identical winning time\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Slow times were expected in \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009921 because of training being impacted by the pandemic.)\", \"from\": 5462, \"to\": 5549, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Slow times\", \"from\": 5463, \"to\": 5473}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5516}, {\"ngram\": \"the pandemic\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Comparing 2024 gold-medal times to 2016, eight have been slower and six faster (one, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 800 freestyle, wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t contested in the Olympics until 2021).\", \"from\": 5550, \"to\": 5709, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2024 gold-medal times\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5581}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 800 freestyle\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5660}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5684, \"to\": 5696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What has it taken to get on the podium?\", \"from\": 5711, \"to\": 5750, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 5739, \"to\": 5749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze-medal times this Olympics have been faster than Tokyo in seven events, slower in seven and the same in one.\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5810, \"end\": 5815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999735135960517, \"rank\": 0.0002649335839525176, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bronze-medal times\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5773}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympics\", \"from\": 5774, \"to\": 5787}, {\"ngram\": \"seven events\", \"from\": 5819, \"to\": 5831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the strong majority have been faster in Paris than in Rio.\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 5932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5914, \"end\": 5919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.944289511376445e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5928, \"end\": 5931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.456643252440618e-23, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the strong majority\", \"from\": 5874, \"to\": 5893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And what has it taken to reach the eight-lane championship final?\", \"from\": 5934, \"to\": 5999, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the eight-lane championship final\", \"from\": 5965, \"to\": 5998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nine eight-place qualifying times have been slower than in Tokyo, while six have been faster.\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6059, \"end\": 6064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999735135960517, \"rank\": 0.0002649335839525176, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nine eight-place qualifying times\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The comparison of 2024 to '16 goes the opposite way, with 11 times faster and three slower.\", \"from\": 6094, \"to\": 6185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The comparison\", \"from\": 6094, \"to\": 6108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seems clear that the sport has gotten deeper since Rio.\", \"from\": 6187, \"to\": 6245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6241, \"end\": 6244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.456643252440618e-23, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 6207, \"to\": 6216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There simply are more fast swimmers, which is a credit to the world at large.\", \"from\": 6246, \"to\": 6323, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more fast swimmers\", \"from\": 6263, \"to\": 6281}, {\"ngram\": \"a credit\", \"from\": 6292, \"to\": 6300}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(And also helps explain why the United States has a fistful of silver at this point instead of gold.)\", \"from\": 6324, \"to\": 6425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6356, \"end\": 6369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9994020471969991, \"rank\": 0.0005975776173603762, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fistful\", \"from\": 6374, \"to\": 6383}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 6387, \"to\": 6393}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 6397, \"to\": 6407}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 6419, \"to\": 6423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But for whatever reason, the times that are winning gold medals here are not measuring up.\", \"from\": 6426, \"to\": 6516, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"whatever reason\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6449}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 6451, \"to\": 6460}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 6478, \"to\": 6489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One coach wonders whether front-runners are paying a price in terms of unusual wave turbulence, setting them up to tire and be passed later in races.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think anyone has won a final or semifinal at 200 meters or less leading the race start to finish,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the coach says.\", \"from\": 6518, \"to\": 6799, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One coach\", \"from\": 6518, \"to\": 6527}, {\"ngram\": \"front-runners\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6557}, {\"ngram\": \"a price\", \"from\": 6569, \"to\": 6576}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 6580, \"to\": 6585}, {\"ngram\": \"unusual wave turbulence\", \"from\": 6589, \"to\": 6612}, {\"ngram\": \"tire\", \"from\": 6633, \"to\": 6637}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 6661, \"to\": 6666}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 6688, \"to\": 6694}, {\"ngram\": \"200 meters\", \"from\": 6727, \"to\": 6737}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 6754, \"to\": 6762}, {\"ngram\": \"the coach\", \"from\": 6783, \"to\": 6792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fascinating.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Fascinating and factual, at least in finals.\", \"from\": 6800, \"to\": 6871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fascinating.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Fascinating\", \"from\": 6810, \"to\": 6837}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 6863, \"to\": 6869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold medalists in every race of 200 meters or shorter have not led coming out of the final turn.\", \"from\": 6872, \"to\": 6972, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gold medalists\", \"from\": 6872, \"to\": 6890}, {\"ngram\": \"every race\", \"from\": 6894, \"to\": 6904}, {\"ngram\": \"200 meters\", \"from\": 6908, \"to\": 6918}, {\"ngram\": \"the final turn\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 6971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Popovici in the 200 freestyle\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094was even in second.\", \"from\": 6973, \"to\": 7035, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only one\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Popovici\", \"from\": 6973, \"to\": 6992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest were in third or fourth with 50 meters to go.\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rest\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7044}, {\"ngram\": \"50 meters\", \"from\": 7074, \"to\": 7083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The semifinals\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094when the competition is slightly less deep\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094has been a bit different.\", \"from\": 7092, \"to\": 7179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The semifinals\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094when\", \"from\": 7092, \"to\": 7113}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 7114, \"to\": 7129}, {\"ngram\": \"deep\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094has\", \"from\": 7147, \"to\": 7157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eleven semifinal winners led at the final turn, while nine semi winners have come from behind.\", \"from\": 7180, \"to\": 7274, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Eleven semifinal winners\", \"from\": 7180, \"to\": 7204}, {\"ngram\": \"the final turn\", \"from\": 7212, \"to\": 7226}, {\"ngram\": \"nine semi winners\", \"from\": 7234, \"to\": 7251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to the naked eye and by the numbers, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to deny that there have been several surprising fades late in races by accomplished swimmers.\\u00c2 Perhaps the waves beat them down.\", \"from\": 7275, \"to\": 7457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the naked eye\", \"from\": 7282, \"to\": 7295}, {\"ngram\": \"the numbers\", \"from\": 7303, \"to\": 7314}, {\"ngram\": \"it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 7316, \"to\": 7322}, {\"ngram\": \"several surprising fades\", \"from\": 7357, \"to\": 7381}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 7390, \"to\": 7395}, {\"ngram\": \"accomplished swimmers\", \"from\": 7399, \"to\": 7420}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 7421, \"to\": 7422}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 7431, \"to\": 7440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There certainly figures to be more of them in the shorter races, when swimmers are at peak speeds and exertion levels and thus creating the most waves and whitewater.\", \"from\": 7458, \"to\": 7624, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the shorter races\", \"from\": 7504, \"to\": 7521}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 7528, \"to\": 7536}, {\"ngram\": \"peak speeds\", \"from\": 7544, \"to\": 7555}, {\"ngram\": \"exertion levels\", \"from\": 7560, \"to\": 7575}, {\"ngram\": \"the most waves\", \"from\": 7594, \"to\": 7608}, {\"ngram\": \"whitewater\", \"from\": 7613, \"to\": 7623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also follows that it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to break world records coming from off the pace.\", \"from\": 7626, \"to\": 7707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 7647, \"to\": 7653}, {\"ngram\": \"world records\", \"from\": 7668, \"to\": 7681}, {\"ngram\": \"the pace\", \"from\": 7698, \"to\": 7706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generally speaking, swimmers capable of being the fastest ever in a certain event get ahead early, stay ahead and win.\", \"from\": 7708, \"to\": 7826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 7728, \"to\": 7736}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain event\", \"from\": 7774, \"to\": 7789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a time-obsessed sport, the Slow Pool Theory will continue to be watched closely and discussed at length.\", \"from\": 7828, \"to\": 7935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a time-obsessed sport\", \"from\": 7831, \"to\": 7852}, {\"ngram\": \"the Slow Pool Theory\", \"from\": 7854, \"to\": 7874}, {\"ngram\": \"length\", \"from\": 7928, \"to\": 7934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could we actually go an entire Olympics without a world record in swimming?\", \"from\": 7936, \"to\": 8011, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an entire Olympics\", \"from\": 7957, \"to\": 7975}, {\"ngram\": \"a world record\", \"from\": 7984, \"to\": 7998}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 8002, \"to\": 8010}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Will the come-from-behind trend continue?\\u00c2 That remains to be seen.\", \"from\": 8012, \"to\": 8080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trend\", \"from\": 8038, \"to\": 8043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s useful to remember that at the Olympics, time doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t matter nearly as much as place.\", \"from\": 8081, \"to\": 8179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"But it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 8081, \"to\": 8091}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 8119, \"to\": 8131}, {\"ngram\": \"doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t matter\", \"from\": 8138, \"to\": 8154}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 8173, \"to\": 8178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every swimmer in Paris would be happy to be the slowest winner of all-time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094as long as they have a gold medal around their neck.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTimes do not matter,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said American freestyler Paige Madden.\", \"from\": 8180, \"to\": 8377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8197, \"end\": 8202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.944289511376445e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 8344, \"end\": 8352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999997940904, \"rank\": 2.008056071106535e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 8364, \"end\": 8376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Every swimmer\", \"from\": 8180, \"to\": 8193}, {\"ngram\": \"the slowest winner\", \"from\": 8224, \"to\": 8242}, {\"ngram\": \"all-time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094as\", \"from\": 8246, \"to\": 8259}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 8278, \"to\": 8290}, {\"ngram\": \"their neck\", \"from\": 8298, \"to\": 8308}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTimes\", \"from\": 8309, \"to\": 8319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt's all about place at the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 8378, \"to\": 8419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 8378, \"to\": 8383}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 8396, \"to\": 8401}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 8405, \"to\": 8417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 8421, \"to\": 8447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Loading recommendations\", \"from\": 8421, \"to\": 8444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations Pat Forde is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated who covers college football and colle